query:
SET @sjc_id = (SELECT id FROM counties WHERE name LIKE '%San Joaquin%' AND state = 'California' LIMIT 1);

-- Adult Trauma protocols
INSERT INTO protocolChunks (countyId, protocolNumber, protocolTitle, section, content, sourcePdfUrl, protocolEffectiveDate, protocolYear, createdAt)
VALUES 
(@sjc_id, 'ATRA-01', 'Trauma', 'Adult Trauma', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Trauma. Primary and secondary survey, hemorrhage control, spinal immobilization, and rapid transport.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),
(@sjc_id, 'ATRA-02', 'Traumatic Arrest', 'Adult Trauma', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Traumatic Arrest. Addressing reversible causes, bilateral needle decompression, and rapid transport.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),

-- Obstetrical protocols
(@sjc_id, 'AOBG-01', 'Childbirth', 'Obstetrical', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Childbirth. Normal delivery, cord clamping, newborn care, and placenta delivery.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),
(@sjc_id, 'AOBG-02', 'Eclampsia & Preeclampsia', 'Obstetrical', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Eclampsia and Preeclampsia. Magnesium sulfate, seizure management, and blood pressure control.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),
(@sjc_id, 'AOBG-03', 'Obstetrical Emergencies', 'Obstetrical', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Obstetrical Emergencies including cord prolapse, breech presentation, and postpartum hemorrhage.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),
(@sjc_id, 'AOBG-04', 'Postpartum Care', 'Obstetrical', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Postpartum Care. Uterine massage, oxytocin administration, and hemorrhage management.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),

-- Adult Overdose protocols
(@sjc_id, 'AODP-01', 'Acute Dystonic Reactions', 'Adult Overdose', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Acute Dystonic Reactions. Diphenhydramine administration and supportive care.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),
(@sjc_id, 'AODP-02', 'Beta Blocker Overdose', 'Adult Overdose', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Beta Blocker Overdose. Glucagon, calcium, and vasopressor support.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),
(@sjc_id, 'AODP-03', 'Calcium Channel Blocker Overdose', 'Adult Overdose', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Calcium Channel Blocker Overdose. Calcium, glucagon, and vasopressor support.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),
(@sjc_id, 'AODP-04', 'Acute Drug Intoxication', 'Adult Overdose', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Acute Drug Intoxication. Supportive care, airway management, and specific antidotes.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),
(@sjc_id, 'AODP-05', 'Cyclic Antidepressant Overdose', 'Adult Overdose', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Cyclic Antidepressant Overdose. Sodium bicarbonate, seizure management, and cardiac monitoring.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),
(@sjc_id, 'AODP-06', 'Opiate Overdose', 'Adult Overdose', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Opiate Overdose. Naloxone administration, airway management, and ventilatory support.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),
(@sjc_id, 'AODP-07', 'Organophosphate Exposure', 'Adult Overdose', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Organophosphate Exposure. Atropine, pralidoxime, and decontamination.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),

-- Adult General protocols
(@sjc_id, 'AGEN-01', 'Sepsis', 'Adult General', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Sepsis. Early recognition, fluid resuscitation, and rapid transport.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),
(@sjc_id, 'AGEN-02', 'Patients From Out Patient Offices', 'Adult General', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Patients From Outpatient Offices. Assessment and continuation of care.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),
(@sjc_id, 'AGEN-03', 'Pain Management', 'Adult General', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Pain Management. Fentanyl, morphine, and non-pharmacological interventions.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),
(@sjc_id, 'AGEN-04', 'Nausea', 'Adult General', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Nausea. Ondansetron administration and supportive care.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW());
